events.name: GDG Iasi - Better Android

venue.name: Sediul Maxcode
venue.address_1: et. 1, Bulevardul Profesor Dimitrie Mangeron 53, Iași 700050

events.description:
We are hosting a gathering to talk about a better world for Android. There will be 2 talks:

1. MVP in Android, by Victor Grădinescu

As the Android platform has evolved to its maturity, Android projects now need larger teams, separation of control, modularity and testability. In this presentation we’re going to discuss about the Model View Presenter pattern and how can it be applied in Android Apps.

A few words about Victor:

As an entrepreneur since the early versions of iPhone and Android, I’ve been developing many native Mobile Apps, either consumer or enterprise oriented. I've also built Enterprise Web Apps and did research in Vehicular Computing before that.

2. Testing mobile in the cloud, by Andrei Diaconu

Android has a fragmented ecosystem. There are devices out there with square screens or even no 3G antenna. It's impossible to test on all of them. But if we write automated tests, then maybe we could run these tests on hundreds of real devices in the cloud. Let's compare Espresso to Appium and Amazon Device Farm to Firebase Device Lab and see which of these we like more.

The event is happening on September 28th, at 18:00 at the Maxcode office - https://goo.gl/maps/cYkqCtA7Juz

Keep in touch with us:

• Google+: https://plus.google.com/11808355420434900520

• Facebook: https://www.facebook.com/gdg.iasi

• Meetup: http://www.meetup.com/Google-Developer-Group-Iasi

events.name: GDG Iasi - Firebase meetup

venue.name: Școala Informală de IT, Aria Office Center, Et 5

events.description:
We are hosting a meetup to discuss the coolest stuffs that Firebase can offer to web developers, android and ios developers, and backend developers.

1. Firebase Keynote, by Bogdan Botea

Join us to get the updates from the Firebase Dev Summit regarding latest Firebase services - Firebase Analytics, Firebase Test Lab for Android, Firebase Crash Reporting, Firebase UI, Firebase Realtime Database and many more.

2. Building an app without backend, by Emilian Damian and Alex Chelariu

Have you ever wanted to try a quick idea of a web app or a ios/android app but needed a backend or a storage service?

We'll show how easy it is to develop your app using the core Firebase back-end services.

P.S. We will also present you an opportunity to win a fully funded ticket to Google I/O 2017, so please make sure you attend.

events.name: Clustering Jenkins with Kubernetes in Google Container Engine
events.description:
GDG is proud to host four presentations at @codeCampRO on the 13th of May! We want to share our knowledge and broaden your perspective on the power of Google Technologies.

This enlightening presentation will be a smooth collaboration between Vlad, a dev-ops miracle worker, hungry for the latest technologies, and Alex whose technical skills (and laughter) will knock your socks off; so you can imagine how dev-ops and developers alike will savor this partnership to the max.

Google Container Engine is a managed service that uses Kubernetes as its underlying container orchestration tool. Jenkins masters, slaves, and any containerized application running in the Container Engine will benefit from automatic health checks and restarts of unhealthy containers. They will demonstrate how easy is to set up Jenkins cluster in GKE and how it continuously can deploy microservices.

Note: To get in, you need a free Code Camp ticket, which you can get here: https://www.eventbrite.com/e/codecamp-iasi-spring-2017-day-2-registration-31349859273

events.name: Android Architecture and Kotlin
events.description:
Google IO brought us Architecture Components and official support for Kotlin. Now that we had some time to play around with the new Architecture Components, we can discuss, exchange ideas, express opinions. The story with Kotlin is a bit different, as there are members of our comunity using it in tests or even production applications for some time. We will be discussing about this also.

So the agenda for this meetup is:

- Room for SQL

- Room vs Realm

- LiveData and reactive architecture

- LiveData vs RxJava

- Lifecycle - decoupling Activities

- KotlinKotlin vs Java + RetroLambda

- Beer vs water

The format is going to be non-formal and focused on having a good time.

See you at Beer Zone, Tuesday at 18:30!

events.name: Meet DevFest at Codecamp
events.description:
Meet GDG DevFest Romania - Iasi 2017 at Codecamp - 10 percent discount tickets!

Speakers, agenda and tickets: https://devfest.ro

Codecamp is co-organiser of GDG DevFest Romania 2017 - otherwise known as "The biggest Google tech conference in Romania". 

The event is at its third annual edition and it brings together the national developer community, each year in a different city, with the aim of learning Google technologies. This year's edition takes place in Iasi, on November 17. 

Over 16 national & international Rockstar Speakers will be tackling hot topics like:

Cloud Computing: Google Cloud Platform, Docker & Containers, TensorFlow, Vision API, Speech API, Machine Learning;

Progressive Web: Web frameworks, Progressive Web apps, AngularJs, HTML5, CSS3, JavaScript, best practices, Polymer Rail, Node.js, React.js;

VR/AR, Daydream, Project tango, Unity, Unreal, Google Play Game services
User experience design;
Android: frameworks & libraries for native mobile apps. Kotlin, RxJava, Data Binding, Testing, best practices for architectures.

3 IMPORTANT things you need to know:

Early bird lasts until October 31st - tickets cost 50 euros if you hurry up!
Student tickets cost 30 euros and will be available depending on the number of seats. 
Given that Codecamp is co-organiser for the event, all Codecamp participants get 10% off (champagne, fireworks, and party hats! :) ) 

What you need to do is register and attend the Codecamp Iași, 28 October 2017

events.name: Google Cloud Next '19 & I/O Extended

#GDG Iasi #io19Extended #GoogleNext19Extended
